Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities are not stated directly but can be derived using:  
  Total Liabilities = Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity – Total Owner's Equity  
  = 21662106.19 – 16146127.58  
  = 5515978.61  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 5515978.61 / 16146127.58  
  ≈ 0.3413 → 0.34

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement:  
  Net Profit = 146127.58  
  Total Revenue = 863371.65  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (146127.58 / 863371.65) × 100%  
  ≈ 16.93%

Step 3: Calculate Return on Assets (ROA)  
• From the balance sheet, Total Assets at end = 21662106.19  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (146127.58 / 21662106.19) × 100%  
  ≈ 0.675% → 0.68%

Step 4: Calculate Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Accounts Receivable at beginning was 0 and at end is 330748.44  
  Assume Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 330748.44) / 2  
  = 165374.22  
• From the income statement, Total Revenue = 863371.65  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 863371.65 / 165374.22  
  ≈ 5.22

The final answer in the required JSON format is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.34",
    "Net Profit Margin": "16.93%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "0.68%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "5.22"
  }
}
